# LawTrace HK — agent rules

These rules apply only to LawTrace paths. Do not change RegLens behaviour for unrelated paths.

## Locked product claim

Supported promise only:

> Compare two official open-data versions of a Hong Kong legislative section and inspect what changed.

Required status language:

> LawTrace displays transformations of open data obtained through DATA.GOV.HK. LawTrace output is for information and research only and is not a verified copy of legislation. Users requiring an official verified copy should consult Hong Kong e-Legislation.

Use: “Official open-data snapshot dated [date].”

## Prohibited claims (binding)

Do not claim or imply:

- law in force on a selected date;
- that a snapshot date is a commencement or effective date;
- verified-copy status;
- legal conclusiveness of automated identity matching;
- legal advice or legislative intent;
- normative importance from change frequency;
- public-health effects inferred from textual changes;
- completeness where a dataset is sampled.

Never display a generic “complete” label for sampled data. If sampled, state the sample explicitly (e.g. “30 of 101”).

## Provenance and comparison

- Preserve source hashes and provenance on every comparison.
- Comparisons must be deterministic for the same inputs and comparator version.
- Reconstruction must pass for supported complete pairs before ordinary display.
- Fail closed on unsupported / potentially_lossy renderability for ordinary complete redlines.
- Do not accept ambiguous identity (splits, consolidations, fuzzy succession) as confirmed.
- Prefer stable source `@id` for top-level section identity only.

## Sources

- Official DATA.GOV.HK / HKeL open-data XML only through the approved acquisition path.
- Do not scrape HKeL HTML, use unofficial mirrors, or fabricate statutory text.
- Cap. 599G local-real artifacts stay gitignored; Cap. 614 demo fixtures may be tracked.
- No raw ZIP/bulk XML under `apps/lawtrace/public/data/`.

## RegLens isolation

- LawTrace is a sibling product: no RegLens domain schema, publication pipeline, or Pages coupling.
- Worker lives under `services/lawtrace-worker/` only.
- Do not auto-publish LawTrace to GitHub Pages or any public static host from ordinary workflows.

## Local review workspace

- Named “Local review workspace”; not in ordinary navigation.
- Included only when explicitly enabled (`LAWTRACE_LOCAL_REVIEW=1` / `make lawtrace-open-local`).
- Ordinary CI/demo builds must exclude `/review` and `/audit`.
- Reviewer CONFIRM/REJECT/UNCERTAIN stays local; never write “human-confirmed” into source artifacts automatically.

## Testing and release

- Run `pytest tests/lawtrace` and reconstruction/determinism checks for worker changes.
- Run `make lawtrace-ci` (or equivalent) before merge for LawTrace UI/data changes.
- Keep RegLens `make verify` green when touching shared Makefile/CI surfaces.
- No public product launch and no LLM explanation layer without an explicit separate approval.
- Prefer `make lawtrace-doctor` then `make lawtrace-open` for local preview.

## Agent startup (LawTrace work)

1. Inspect branch and working tree.
2. Run `make lawtrace-doctor`.
3. Read latest Stage E / limitations and `docs/LAWTRACE_OPERATIONS.md`.
4. Identify the smallest measurable objective.
5. Implement.
6. Run deterministic and reconstruction checks.
7. Run product QA on the running site.
8. Update LawTrace docs/reports.
9. Never broaden legal claims autonomously.
